  "text": "The Color Quality Scale (CQS) [CITATION_1] is a method which mixes color fidelity and people's preference for chroma enhancement, by using more saturated test-color samples. The CQS does not penalize (nor reward) for increased chroma, includes improvements for chromatic adaptation, and uses a more homogeneous color space in evaluating color differences.",
